t for next time.","Dashi, or Japanese cooking stock, adds flavour to the chawan mushi. You can replace the instant dashi powder with <nobr>½ tsp homemade<\/nobr> chicken or vegetable stock paste: first dilute the stock paste in some of the water before adding it in <nobr>step 1,<\/nobr> and reduce salt to <nobr>¼ tsp.<\/nobr> Or omit dashi powder and use <nobr>300 g stock<\/nobr> instead of water in <nobr>step 1.<\/nobr> Finally you can omit the dashi powder altogether; the dish will have a more subtle egg flavour."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","35m","6 portions"]}